  "texts": [
    "(16), r and s shows real and synthetic images while r, Σ r and s, Σ s denote mean and covariances of real and synthetic images.",
    "FID score measures the distance between real and synthetic images in GANs.",
    "A higher FID score shows a larger distance between synthetic and real data distributions (Borji 2019).",
    "In GANs, PSNR is used to check the quality of synthetic images to the corresponding real images.",
    "PSNR is applied to monochrome images."
